UID:5525-1775307600-1775318400@bloomspinweave.org
SUMMARY:Beginning Wheel Spinning with Nelly DeVault
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, April 4th\, 2026\, 1:00 – 4:00 PM \nIn this class\, students will begin by learning the basics of spinning wheel function and will leave with their own hand-spun yarn!  This class is designed for new beginners\, but any spinners are welcome\, whether you can’t get along with your wheel or want help trouble-shooting any specific spinning issues. You may borrow a wheel or bring your own.  Spinning fibers will be provided. \n  \n$55- BSWG members \n$65 – non-BSWG student members (includes one-year guild student membership) \n$85 – non-BSWG members (includes one-year guild membership) \n  \nThis is a beginner level workshop. \nTo register\, click here. \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/beginning-wheel-spinning-with-nelly-devault
LOCATION:Fiber Arts Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington\, 3038 East Third Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bloomspinweave.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/26-4-4-Wheel-spining-with-Nelly-scaled.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Guild":MAILTO:educationbswg@gmail.com, newsletterbswg@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
